title: The Dried-up Fountain
creator: Robert Leighton
description: LibriVox LibriVox volunteers bring you 15 recordings of The Dried-up Fountain by Robert Leighton. This was the Fortnightly Poetry project for December 18, 2011. This poem is taken from A Victorian Anthology, 1837–1895, Edmund Clarence Stedman, ed. (1833–1908). (Summary by David Lawrence) For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording. For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org. Download M4B (16MB)
subject: librivox; literature; audiobook; poetry; romance; fantasy; myths/legends; nature
source: Librivox recording of a public-domain text
